com.steelypip.powerups.hydraxml

Interface HydraXML

  • All Superinterfaces:
    HydraNode<java.lang.String,java.lang.String,java.lang.String,HydraXML>, java.lang.Iterable<java.util.Map.Entry<java.lang.String,HydraXML>>, MultiAttributes<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>, MultiLinks<java.lang.String,HydraXML>, Named
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BadHydraXML, FlexiHydraXML

    public interface HydraXML
extends HydraNode<java.lang.String,java.lang.String,java.lang.String,HydraXML>
    HydraXML is a multi-valued extension of MinXML that, in its turn, is a cleaner, leaner, cut-down version of XML with only the absolute essentials. An HydraXML object is a single node or 'element' that represents a multi-valued tree of elements, where each element is a named, multi-valued dictionary. The HydraXML interface defines a standard interface for all classes representing HydraXML elements. HydraXML elements support freezing and unfreezing via freeze, shallowCopy and frozenCopy. Freezing is a promise from the programmer that no further updates will be applied; it is advisory insofar that the implementation can ignore a freeze.

      • freeze

        void freeze()
        A programmer directed promise that no further modifications will be made to this object. The implementation is encouraged but not required to detect any further modifications. In the event that a broken promise is detected, the effect will be a thrown UnsupportedOperationException. There is no unfreeze counterpart, in order that implementations are encouraged to take advantage of store sharing.
